Originally the {{m|ja|йҖЈз”ЁеҪў|tr=ren'yЕҚkei||stem or continuative form}} of verb {{m|ja|йӢҸгӮҖ|tr=hasamu||to be tightly between two things, to be inserted in betweenвҖқ}},<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref> itself apparently deriving from ''hasa'' (вҖңnarrowness between other thingsвҖқ, likely cognate with {{m|ja|зҙ°|tr=hoso}}, вҖңskinny, narrowness within the thing itselfвҖқ) + auxiliary suffix {{m|ja|гӮҖ|tr=mu||to be or become like something}}.

Cognate and homophonic with {{m|ja|жҢҹ}}, {{m|ja|жҢҝ|tr=hasami}}: вҖңbeing stuck in between other thingsвҖқ.

